025). Each engaged with this dictum in unique and novel ways, and in so doing anticipated a number of central features of Avicenna’s writings. The history of this argument is of crucial importance for understanding the evolution of natural philosophy and metaphysics in this formative period, away from tedious and simplistic arguments about creation and towards a more robust modal ontology based on intrinsic and extrinsic necessity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aPhilosophy, ArabxGreek influences. 4aBeweis. 4aEpistemologie. 4aKontingenz. 4aNaturphilosophie. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  acontingency.  ademonstration.  aepistemology.  anatural philosophy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1z978311133219208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishz978311131928508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831113251320 cprintz978311132492040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311132508840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111325088423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111325088/original  a978-3-11-131928-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-133219-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2024 Part 1b2024  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_CL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  